{
  "text": "In order to bring into focus additional pollen functions and proteins that are affected by HS, on one hand, and those that participate in the protection of DPGs from HS, on the other hand, the following analyses were undertaken. The differentially expressed proteins in the four sample/treatment comparisons (P-HS vs. P-C, P-E-HS vs. P-HS, P-E-C vs. P-C, and P-E-HS vs. P-C) were analyzed for GO-category enrichment relative to the tomato genome database using Plant MetGen Map [CITATION_1] ) and results of significantly enriched GO terms (FDR \u2264 0.05) in the BP category (found to be most informative) are presented in Supplementary Tables S7. The data was used in order to identify unique functional terms for each comparison and results are presented in Figure 6 and Supplementary Table S8, highlighting functions and proteins that were not discussed in the previous sections.",
  "citation_candidates": [
